                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <height  min="4" max="5" unit = "cm">4-5</height>
                                <note type="palaeographic" xml:id="en">
                                    <p>
                                        Rightward ductus, horizontal alignment, vertical letter module, irregular <term xml:lang="la">ductus</term>, triangular punctuation, deep incision, and leftward layout.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        The letter <g type="pl">M</g> is composed of four oblique strokes and has a square module.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        The lapicide made several layout errors: the final <g type="pl">I</g> at the end of the first two lines was carved onto the right frame margin.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        The <g type="pl">E</g> is markedly compressed laterally
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        The <g type="pl">F</g> has an unusual lower crossbar placed beneath the main crossbar and is distinguished from the <hi rend="italic">E</hi> by its upper arm, which is oblique and rises toward the right.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        The <g type="pl">M</g> consists of four oblique shafts
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        The <g type="pl">N</g> shows oblique lateral shafts
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        the <g type="pl">Q</g> bears a short, thin tail.
                                    </p>
                                </note>
                                <note type="palaeographic" xml:id="it">
                                    <p>
                                        Verso destrorso, andamento orizzontale, modulo verticale, <term xml:lang="la">ductus</term> irregolare, interpunzione triangoliforme, solco profondo e impaginazione a sinistra.
                                    </p> 
                                    <p>
                                        Il lapicida ha commesso vari errori di impaginazione: le lettere <g type="pl">I</g> alla fine delle prime due righe sono state incise sul margine destro della cornice.
                                    </p> 
                                    <p>
                                        La <g type="pl">E</g> è fortemente compressa lateralmente.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        La <g type="pl">F</g> presenta un insolito braccio inferiore posto sotto la cravatta e si distingue dalla <g type="pl">E</g> per il braccio superiore obliquo, ascendente verso destra.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        La <g type="pl">M</g> è composta da quattro aste oblique.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        La <g type="pl">N</g> mostra aste laterali oblique.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        La <g type="pl">Q</g> presenta una coda corta e sottile.
                                    </p>
                                </note>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
