            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="Latin">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/>Arca <persName ref="#numerianus">Numeriani</persName> pr<choice><corr>i</corr><sic>e</sic></choice>ncipalis de ci
                        <lb n="2" break="no"/>vitate Murse<supplied reason="omitted">n</supplied>se, annorum <num value="30">XXX</num>, quod si
                        <lb n="3"/>aliquis eam <choice><reg>arcam</reg><orig>arca</orig></choice> aperire voluerit, da
                        <lb n="4" break="no"/><w xml:id="w1"><choice><reg>bit</reg><orig>vet</orig></choice></w> fisco <measure type="fine" unit="uncia" commodity="gold" quantity="6">auri uncias sex.</measure>
                    </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app loc="4" from="#w1">
                        <lem>
                            <choice><reg>bit</reg><orig>vet</orig></choice>
                        </lem>
                        <rdg source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8746 #ilcv3607 #edr097744">
                            <choice><reg>bit</reg><orig>vit</orig></choice>
                        </rdg>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p xml:lang="en">
                    The sarcophagus of <persName xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName>, <term xml:lang="la">principalis</term> of the city of <placeName xml:lang="la">Mursese</placeName>, aged thirty. If anyone should wish to open this sarcophagus, they shall pay <measure type="fine" unit="uncia" commodity="gold" quantity="6">six ounces of gold</measure> to the <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term>.
                </p>
                <p xml:lang="it">
                    Arca di <persName corresp="#numerianus" xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName>, <term xml:lang="la">principalis</term> della città di <placeName xml:lang="la">Mursese</placeName>, di trent’anni. Se qualcuno vorrà aprire questa arca, dovrà versare al <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term> <measure type="fine" unit="uncia" commodity="gold" quantity="6">sei once d’oro</measure>.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                    <p>
                        <persName ref="#numerianus" xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName> was a <term xml:lang="la">principalis</term>, an honorary rank which, in Late Antiquity, did not correspond to a specific office but was conferred upon members of local <term xml:lang="la">curiae</term>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <persName ref="#numerianus" xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName> came from the city of <placeName>Mursa</placeName> in Pannonia, today’s Esseg-Osijek.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        According to <bibl ref="#hoffmann1963">Hoffmann</bibl>, <persName ref="#numerianus" xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName> travelled to <placeName>Concordia</placeName> in the retinue of <persName>Theodosius</persName>, together with <persName ref="./Saturninus.xml/#saturninus" xml:lang="la">Saturninus</persName>, for the same purpose: to reorganize the territory after the Battle of the <placeName>Frigidus</placeName>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        If <bibl ref="#hoffmann1963">Hoffmann</bibl>’s hypothesis is accepted, the inscription would date to 394 AD or to the years immediately following. However, the paleographic features of the letterforms seem to suggest an earlier date.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div type="commentary" xml:lang="it">
                    <p>
                        <persName ref="#numerianus" xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName> era un <term xml:lang="la">principalis</term>, una dignità onoraria che nella tarda antichità non indicava una carica precisa, ma era attribuita ai membri delle curie locali.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <persName ref="#numerianus" xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName> proveniva dalla città di <placeName>Mursa</placeName> in Pannonia, l’odierna Esseg-Osijek.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <bibl ref="#hoffmann1963">Hoffmann</bibl> ritiene che <persName ref="#numerianus" xml:lang="la">Numerianus</persName> si fosse diretto a <placeName>Concordia</placeName> al seguito di <persName>Theodosius</persName> assieme a <persName ref="./Saturninus.xml/#saturninus" xml:lang="la">Saturninus</persName> per la stessa ragione: riorganizzare il territorio dopo la battaglia del <placeName>Frigido</placeName>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Se si considera l’ipotesi di <bibl ref="#hoffmann1963">Hoffmann</bibl>, l’epigrafe sarebbe riconducibile al 394 d.C. o agli anni immediatamente successivi. Tuttavia, le caratteristiche paleografiche delle lettere sembrano suggerire una datazione più antica.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
